<br>
Caster's nuking power was dependent not just on having mana or the spell, but how often they used that spell or that casting type.<br>
<br>
How about your character slowly forgetting old skills you haven't kept sharp while you spent every waking moment learning that new skill.  (example.. maybe a rogue hasn't picked a lock in 10 game years, but has been trying to learn to track like mad.)<br>
<br>
I'd like the type of material your armor is made out of affect it's armor rating, not just some AC number the zone designer decided.  I'd like to see class restrictions enforced on a piece of equipment, uh.. like seeing druids walk around in platemail /boggle.<br>
<br>
How about a tradeskill system where the skill or time the player spent with the piece affected the final piece's quality?<br>
<br>
Most of all, I'd like to see an experience system reflect usage of your abilities, not just being in the group when the mob hits the ground and stops breathing.  If your a cleric, your experience comes from healing.. enchanter? comes from mezzing or enchanting.  Melee? yep.. each strike of the blade yields xp for them.<br>
<br>
And, sorry.. but we only need 1 backpack.. just make it have the necessary size to hold so much weight. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425876" target="top"><br>
