<br>
Of course it was nothing like that.<br>
<br>
Pre Kurnik, so no POP books, and not that many porters either, so everyone was isolated. The humanoid team dominated west Antonica, the evil team east Antonica. Freeport was a ghost town, you make a human, start in Qeynos or you're screwed. We talked about taking Freeport back, but how could you really take it back? It would be cool if you could fight over FP or some strategic place like HHP, we'd be on the walls defending it, close the gates, add rams and ballistas. They win, they could sack it, raze it, make it their own.<br>
<br>
You'd be able to build forts. Add resources like mines, lose them and no new weapons for joo. And of course weapons need to wear out. And rogues should be able to sneak into cities, sabatoge stuff, or assasinate vendors or city leaders (who would have some kind of real function.)<br>
<br>
But it's all just a dream. Or is it?? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kestpur>Kestpur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#330000>(12/13/03 1:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1114.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RPG dreaming</span><hr size=1> Isn't that what they tried to do with Shadowbane? PvP, build up and destroy towns, control of the world economy? Not sure if that's how it was fully implimented, but that's how I remember them selling it. <p>======================================================<br>
